name: Crayfish Cornbread
author: debra
summary: One of my favorite Cajun recipes!
ingredients: 1 (12 ounce) package dry corn bread mix
1 (10 ounce) can diced tomatoes with green chile peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Saute crawfish, onions, bell peppers, green onions, salt and pepper together until crawfish are cooked; approximately 5 minutes
Mix together cornbread mix, tomatoes and egg
Pour cornbread mixture and crawfish mixture into a 9x13 inch baking pan
Glaze top of cornbread with butter and sprinkle with cheese
Change the oven's temperature to broil and place the cornbread back in the oven until the cheese has melted, approximately 2 minutes
